PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Black & Decker and the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission jointly recalled about 192,000 random orbit sanders over safety concerns. The black plastic disc that holds the sandpaper can fly off or break apart during use. The company has received 73 reports of such incidents, one of which resulted in a serious facial laceration. The products in question were sold at a number of retailers nationwide from January 2007 through July 2009 for about $40 each. Consumers should stop using the products immediately and contact Black & Decker for a free replacement plate to hold the sandpaper.
